    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-16T07:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-16T07:35:00-05:00" n="312"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.9111/53: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-16T16:00:00+03:25"
                            >March 16, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 16—11:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. Reference Department’s 42, February 23.<note n="63" xml:id="d312fn63">Not
                        printed.</note> There follows a paraphrase of a note just received from
                    Prime Minister:</p>
                <p>Iranian Government states it is unaware of the nature of transactions and
                    Lend-Lease agreements between United States and British and Russian Governments,
                    no mention thereof having been made in the Soviet-British-Iranian Treaty and no
                    connection therewith anticipated. Nevertheless in view of the happy relations
                    existing between Iran and United States the Iranian Government agrees with
                    pleasure that if there are questions the settlement of which are necessary or
                    useful for mutual interests they should in order to safeguard Iranian and
                    American interests be brought up and considered between representatives of the
                    four Governments in connection with the supplementary treaties which will soon
                    be concluded.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
